You can implement the `onMsaCode` callback by passing it in the client options. Here's an example:
js
const bot = mineflayer.createBot({
  username: 'email',
  auth: 'microsoft',
  onMsaCode: (data) => {
    console.log(`Go to ${data.verification_uri} and enter code: ${data.user_code}`);
  }
});

Use the following code to get the trades:
js
const target = bot.nearestEntity((e) => e.name === 'villager');
await bot.lookAt(target.position);
const villager = await bot.openVillager(target);
console.log(villager.trades);

This will log the array of trades for the nearest villager.

